OL,3,CResidents angry at 'river' of sewage
OL,4,Cwater outside their homes
OL,6,FSouthern Water says it's doing all it
OL,7,Fcan to solve the problem.
OL,9,FThe Bridgwaters say the problem first
OL,10,Fstarted three years ago but is getting
OL,11,Fworse.
OL,13,FThey claim the water regularly leaves
OL,14,Fthe drain at a height of 2-3ft.
OL,16,FLouise Bridgwater said: "We have
OL,17,Fsleepless nights and stressful days
OL,18,Fwhen it happens. A 'river' of sewage
OL,19,Fwater at the end of the drive would
OL,20,Fprevent us leaving the house, should
OL,21,Fwe need to leave.
